---
title: Thai Shrimp with Candied Peanuts over Sesame Cabbage & Arugula Salad
description: Salt and pepper. Burgers and fries. Peas and carrots. These classic pairings have stood the test of time. If you’re anything like our chefs, though, you know that one flavor duo trumps all others: sweet and spicy. Here, that sweet heat comes in the form of a finger-licking blend of Thai chili sauce, lime zest, and a bit of butter. It’s all simmered with the sautéed shrimp, then spooned over a refreshing arugula sesame salad and topped with candied peanuts. With dinners like this, life really is sweet (and spicy), friends.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62163d4cbc26543b1811290a-a8758fc3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/thai-shrimp-with-candied-peanuts-62163d4cbc26543b1811290a-b1268f31.pdf
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/thai-shrimp-with-candied-peanuts-62163d4cbc26543b1811290a
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 40 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1300 mg
---

Wash and dry produce. Trim and peel @carrots{6%ounce}(grated on the
largest holes of a box grater); transfer to a large #bowl{}. Trim and halve
@Persian cucumber{1}; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Zest and
quarter @lime{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Heat a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@peanuts{1%ounce}, @sugar{2%teaspoon}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring
often, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a small bowl. Wipe out pan.

To bowl with grated carrots, add cucumber, @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce},
@arugula lettuce{2%ounce}, @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}, and juice from two
lime wedges (four wedges for 4 servings). Toss to combine. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for peanuts over medium-high heat. Once
pan is hot, add shrimp and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp
are opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.
Turn off heat.

Add @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} and half the lime zest to pan with shrimp.
Stir until evenly coated.

Divide salad between plates and top with shrimp. Garnish with candied peanuts
and remaining lime zest. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.